The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                The city and its adjoining areas experienced widespread power cuts on Monday evening as the shortfall in the CESC-served areas shot up to 135 MW. The Bandel thermal power plant and a unit of the Durgapur Projects Limited were shut down. Power cuts are likely to continue on Tuesday.     A passenger lost a cellphone and other valuables in the airports domestic terminal on Monday. Suresh Shah, who came from Mumbai, lodged a police complaint. He went to toilet keeping the valuables on a trolley when they were lifted.    Prasanta Karmakar, 40, was arrested on Sunday night for falsely claiming that a diamond ring worth Rs 6 lakh had been snatched from him on a Metro train on July 17. Police said a woman had given Karmakar the ring for repairs. The ornament was found on him.    The sessions court on Monday shifted the case of former CPI (Maoist) state secretary Somen to a fast-track court. Somens lawyer pleaded for bail and the status of political prisoner for him. The case will be heard again on July 30.    Autorickshaws on the Garia-Gol Park and Jadavpur-Taratala routes were off the road on Monday. Two Citu-backed unions on the routes clashed on Sunday. Nearly 450 vehicles on the Garia-Gol Park route and at least 150 on the Jadavpur-Taratala route did not ply.                                                                                                                                                              
